{"program1": "    dmx[pref[i]] = dp[i]", "program2": "            t *= 2\n            a += 1"}

But note: in program1.py, the line we are replacing is a comment that says "# TODO: Your code here".

Alternatively, we can output the two lines as a single string with a newline in between. So:

{"program1": "                dmx[pref[i]] = dp[i]", "program2": "            t *= 2\n            a += 1"}

But wait, the program2.py code has:

    if a > b:
